author: nehatahani
text:
🍇 enjoy every bite: 

If it doesn’t taste good, don’t eat it.

author: nehatahani
text:
🥝 focus on what matters:

As long as you’re eating real, Whole Foods you can follow any preferred diet.

author: nehatahani
text:
🍳 cook at home:

Most meals from restaurants and fast food places and prepackaged are calorie dense with processed ingredients. When you cool you know what exactly is going into your body.

author: nehatahani
text:
🥥 give up the white stuff: 

Avoid sugar. If you want something sweetened, opt for honey.

author: nehatahani
text:
🍋 prioritize plants: 

Veggies and fruits are rich in vitamins, minerals and nutrients while also being low in calories.

author: nehatahani
text:
🍌 eat what you can pronounce: 

If you can list all the ingredients without going huh? It’s probably clean and free of chemicals.

author: nehatahani
text:
🥕 go organic: 

When you get organic, it’s the cleanest kind of food grown or raised without chemicals.

author: nehatahani
text:
🥬 eat naked:

Foods that don’t come in packages such as fresh fruits and veggies, meats and fish from butchers, grains, nuts and spices you can buy in bulk.

author: nehatahani
text:
🥛 choose just one: 

If a food has just one ingredient it’s clean, nutritious whole food.

author: nehatahani
text:
🍏 eat real. 

Real food is clean food. If it comes from the ground and grown on a farm. It’s nutritious and good for your body.

author: nehatahani
text:
🚲 the rules for 75 days: 

1. wake up before 8am and sleep before 11pm 

2. 1hr daily exercise 

3. consume 1,200 calories or less 

4. 4l of water a day

5. fast 18hrs or more but preferably one meal per day 

6. spend less time online 

7. learn something new each day
